cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE. 

The paper discusses a question answering model that applies to both images and structured knowledge bases, which suggests it could belong to multiple sub-categories. The use of natural language strings and neural networks also points towards cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a likely sub-category. The mention of visual domains and benchmark datasets suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning and joint learning of parameters suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
